The paper deals with model-checking problems for first-order logic on graphs and posets, which are topics typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO), data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific techniques used in the paper, such as the structure theorem for graphs with excluded topological subgraphs and the concept of coloured posets of bounded width, also suggest these categories.
